  "text": "Immunoprecipitation was carried out according to [CITATION_1] . Briefly, newly hatched chick brains were homogenized and extracted in an ice-cold extraction buffer (1% Triton, 1% NP-40, 1 mM EDTA, 1 mM PMSF in 50 mM TBS, pH 7.6) with gentle rocking for 30 min. The extract was centrifuged, and the supernatant was incubated with NCAT2 or control antibody for 1 h, followed by incubation with Sepharose 4B-linked secondary antibody (Zymed Laboratories, Inc., South San Francisco, CA) for 30 min. The bound antigens were released by incubation with 50 mM triethylamine (pH 11.5).",
